-- Access Bank Nigeria Gains to Highest in 17 Months on Profit Bets
-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 2012-09-11T14:59:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-01/access-bank-nigeria-gains-for-3rd-day-rises-most-in-4-weeks-1-.html
Access Bank Plc (ACCESS) , a Nigerian lender,
rose to the highest in 17 months as investors speculate the
company will this week announce higher profit, said Lambeth
Trust Investment Co. Ltd.  The shares gained 2.8 percent to close at 8.74 naira in
Lagos, the commercial capital, the highest since April 2011 and
bringing its advance this year to 82 percent.  “Investors are expecting Access Bank’s second-quarter
result this week and are anticipating higher performance, ”
David Adonri, chief executive officer of Lagos-based Lambeth
said by phone today.  Access Bank has submitted its second-quarter results to the
 Nigerian Stock Exchange  for release, Segun Fafore, a spokesman
for the lender, said by phone.  Net income in the year through to December jumped 51
percent to 16.7 billion naira ($106 million), the Lagos-based
bank said on March 16. Revenue advanced to 138.9 billion naira,
up from 91.1 billion naira a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
